comments: Beverley (LAC) reaches across Booker?s (PHX) body and makes contact to his arm, causing him to lose control of the ball.
After regaining control of the ball, Booker (PHX) gathers the ball, takes two legal steps, but then jumps and returns to the floor without releasing the ball.
Ayton (PHX) maintains a legal guarding position on Morris Sr.?s (LAC) drive to the basket.
Crowder (PHX) reaches across and cleanly blocks Mann's (LAC) shot attempt.

The blocking foul called on Beverly (LAC) was overturned pursuant to a coach?s challenge. Beverly clearly and conclusively established a position in Booker?s (PHX) path prior to the contact and Booker?s upward shooting motion.
Mann (LAC) initiates marginal contact with Bridges (PHX) before separating to get open for the pass.
Although Mann (LAC) is able to complete the shot, Bridges (PHX) makes more than marginal contact with Mann?s arm while he is in his shooting motion.
George (LAC) maintains a legal hand on Paul (PHX) before reaching around with his left hand and hitting Paul in the elbow, which causes Paul to lose control of the ball.
George (LAC) cleanly knocks the ball from Paul?s (PHX) control.
Ayton (PHX), Jackson (LAC) and other players tangle under the rim when attempting to get to the rebound.
George (LAC) is in the paint for at or about three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Jackson (LAC) is in a legal position when there is contact with Paul (PHX) during his drive. Paul does not extend or go through Jackson?s position and Jackson?s momentum carries him forward.
The jump ball called on the out of bounds was overturned pursuant to instant replay review by referees and the ball was awarded to LAC.
Bridges (PHX) commits a take foul on George (LAC).
Saric (PHX) and Crowder (PHX) collide and Saric loses control of the ball. George (LAC) makes some contact with Saric prior to the collision but does not push him into Crowder.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: With 7.8 seconds remaining, Batum cleanly knocked the ball from Payne near the sideline, causing it to go out of bounds. Referees awarded the ball to PHX and since they did not have doubt as to the call, they did not utilize replay. Based on postgame and L2M reviews, there is not clear and conclusive evidence that the call was incorrect.
George (LAC) commits a take foul on Paul (PHX).
Bridges (PHX) makes contact with George's (LAC) arm as he is receiving the inbound pass.
Cousins (LAC) clamps Saric's (PHX) arm while the pair engaging for rebounding position. Any contact from Saric is deemed incidental.
The ball does not hit the rim on Cousins' (LAC) free throw attempt.
Beverley (LAC) moves laterally into Paul?s (PHX) path on his drive, and there is lower leg contact with Paul. The foul precedes any potential traveling violation.
George (LAC) commits a take foul on Paul (PHX).
